    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1087"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas, Venezuela</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                    Venezuelan courts have appointed the appraisers to assess the damages alleged to
                    have been caused the government by the nonfulfillment of the concession <pb
                        facs="1122" n="1002" xml:id="pg_1002"/> of the New York and Bermudez Asphalt
                    Company. The appraisers appointed are: Jesús Muñoz Tebar, Manuel Clemante
                    Urbaneja, Isaías Garbiras.</p>
                <p>Jesús Muñoz Tebar is a civil engineer, Urbaneja is a lawyer, and has been at
                    times connected with the asphalt suits in Venezuela, Garbiras is a civil
                    engineer.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William W. Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
